    </tbody>
  </table>
  <p>In BaZi practice, each Stem has a vivid metaphorical identity. Jiǎ Wood (<span class="chinese-char">甲</span>) is the towering tree &mdash; upright, principled, unbending. Yǐ Wood (<span class="chinese-char">乙</span>) is the vine &mdash; flexible, adaptive, tenacious. Bǐng Fire (<span class="chinese-char">丙</span>) is the sun &mdash; radiant and impossible to conceal. Dīng Fire (<span class="chinese-char">丁</span>) is the candle flame &mdash; intimate, focused, warm. These metaphors are not poetic decoration; they are diagnostic tools used in chart interpretation.</p>
</section>

<section id="earthly-branches">
  <h2>The Twelve Earthly Branches (<span class="chinese-char">地支</span>)</h2>
  <p>The twelve Earthly Branches represent the terrestrial dimension. Each Branch is associated with a <a href="/zodiac/">zodiac animal</a>, a compass direction, a two-hour period of the day, and a month of the year.</p>
